Happy Pride Month! Watch how the King Arthur Baking community is kicking off celebrations. ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜

"We celebrate Pride because we are committed to a more diverse and inclusive future — and we want to show up for each other." - Karen Colberg, King Arthur Baking co-CEO

King Arthur Baking Company is making a donation to @TheTrevorProject, which provides crisis intervention and suicide prevention services to lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, queer & questioning (LGBTQ) young people under 25. We encourage you to learn more and donate at bakewith.us/TrevorProject

node.text: Think cinnamon rolls are out of your baking wheelhouse? Think again! Our own Kye @life.of.kye is here to take you step-by-step through our #recipeoftheyear, Perfectly Pillowy Cinnamon Rolls. With a friend by your virtual side, you’re destined for cinnamon-swirled success! Share your rolls with #recipeoftheyear and #KingArthurBaking

node.title: Bake it Better with Kye: How to make Perfectly Pillowy Cinnamon Rolls

node.accessibility_caption: A tall stack of pancakes whipped with blueberry compote. -Photo by King Arthur Baking

node.text: Stuck in a pancake rut? This twist on our Simply Perfect Pancakes recipe includes masa harina for an intriguing hint of corn flavor. Accompanied with a jammy blueberry-lemon sauce, (which includes a touch of masa harina for body), this stack is ideal for a quick meal — day or night. Find the recipe and grab a bag of our Organic Masa Harina at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking. Share your pancakes with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A top-down shot of two Belgian-Style yeast waffles on a round plate, with toasted walnuts, slices of banana, and maple syrup on top. -Photo by King Arthur Baking

node.text: Every day should be #NationalWaffleDay if you ask us … or Leslie Knope @parksandrec 🧇 Since today is the OFFICIAL holiday, we’re hunkering down with a big stack of crisp and fluffy Belgian-Style Yeast Waffles. Find the recipe at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your waffle stack with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: Biscuits in a cast iron pan with a pastry bush, cup of brown butter, and red and white checked tablecloth. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Can sourdough biscuits really be as easy as 1-2-3 … 4? With PJ’S Casual Sourdough Baker approach, they can! Check out her ultra-simple technique at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and give it a go when you need a quick breakfast or side dish. Share your biscuits with #KingArthurBaking.

node.accessibility_caption: A pandan chiffon cake baked in a tube pan with slices removed to show a fluffy, faintly yellow-green interior. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: With flavors of rose, vanilla, and coconut, pandan leaves are a favorite ingredient @shilpaiyereats reaches for when she’s craving the flavors of Singapore, her childhood home. Whether it’s baked into a springy green and pillowy-soft chiffon cake or another favorite recipe, you’ll want to start baking with pandan ASAP! Read up on Shilpa’s 5 best tips for it by tapping the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your creations with #KingArthurBaking.

node.accessibility_caption: Baking expert, Frank, adds a note on the process of a hit baking mix. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: After months of testing, Frank from our R&D team tells us about the journey it took to create the perfect “just-add-water” pancake mix. With so many factors to consider, there were a lot of failed batches along the way. Step into the Test Kitchen for a behind-the-scenes look by tapping the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your next batch of pancakes with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: Four doughnuts, two pink, on a tray, one with a bite out of it. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Doughnuts aren’t just for breakfast anymore. Made with fruit and served with ice cream, we’ve taken the basic doughnut and turned it into a full-on, decadent dessert. See how it’s done by tapping the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your dessert doughnuts with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: Pati Jinich making tortillas in her kitchen, with a quote from her on a green field underneath: “I’m so impressed with King Arthur’s masa harina. My tortillas puff beautifully and my masa for tamales passes the float test every time.” Photo shared with permission by King Arthur Baking.

node.text:
When making her Tamales Tapatíos inspired by the Mexican state of Jalisco, @PatiJinich of @PBS’s Pati’s Mexican Table was thrilled with the results from our Organic Masa Harina. Pati shared that because of its fine texture and easy workability, “it makes the softest, fluffiest tamales.”

Try out her recipe for Tamales Tapatíos and grab a bag of Organic Masa Harina by tapping the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking. Share your tamales with #KingArthurBaking.

node.accessibility_caption: Pati Jinich making tortillas in her kitchen, with a quote from her on a green field underneath: “I’m so impressed with King Arthur’s masa harina. My tortillas puff beautifully and my masa for tamales passes the float test every time.” Photo shared with permission by King Arthur Baking.
A table set with tamales and condiments. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

A many-layered pastry cut into slices with three seen from above to show brown and white feathered icing on top and one tipped on its side to show all the internal layers. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Though this mille-feuille (also known as a Napoleon) doesn’t quite have 1,000 layers as its French name alludes, its flaky goodness would have you guessing there were 10,000! Try this and other favorites from our best-selling cookbook The Baker’s Companion by tapping the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking for the full collection. Share your bakes with #KingArthurBaking.

node.accessibility_caption: A close up of a cake with a chocolate cake base, a filling made of fresh strawberry slices and chocolate mousse, and topped with chocolate and more fresh berries. -Photo by Raymond Prado

node.text: A good baking project can help make the stress of the week melt away. With simple classics like pasta and bagels to more extravagant options like this gorgeous Chocolate and Strawberry Cream Puff Cake from @gesinebp, our Weekend Baking Adventures recipe collection has a project for you. Find it at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your weekend baking adventures with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A baker kneading dough by hand on the countertop. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking

node.text: How big is the universe? What does it all mean? What IS gluten? These are the questions that keep us up at night. With her baking-nerd cap on, Rossi @abakinggirl is diving into the curious but powerful creature that is gluten. Tap the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking for the scoop, and share your next bake with #KingArthurBaking

Have you heard? Theatre on the Hill is at King Arthur Baking Company here in Norwich, VT! Every weekend through September 12, we’re hosting live outdoor theatre from @jagproductionsvt, here on the hill next to our Cafe, Bakery, Store and Baking School in Norwich, VT! 

We’re proud to partner with JAG Productions from White River Junction, whose mission as a theatre company is to bring compassion, empathy, love, and community through the lens of the African American experience.

JAG will be presenting workshops, concerts, burlesques, and staged readings, each of which illuminates Black life and aesthetics. King Arthur's courtyard opens at 6:30 p.m. ET every Friday, Saturday, and Sunday during the series, where you can enjoy local food and beverages before the show starts at 8 p.m. on the hill. 

Tickets are on sale now! Adult themes and language — parental guidance suggested. For more info and tickets, visit the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking

We hope to see you on the hill!
